info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 09 at 1:14AM MST until November 09 at 2:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...South winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph. * WHERE...Ferris/Seminoe/Shirley Mountains, Central Carbon County, North Snowy Range Foothills and Southwest Carbon County. * WHEN...Until 2 PM MST this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
